WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:13.000
Good afternoon, dear colleagues. I am Oleg Boksansky, Professor of the Russian Economic Academy named after Georgy Plokhanov.

00:13.000 --> 00:25.000
I teach MBA courses in general management, management of organizations, management of human resources, and I am a consultant in the field of HR consulting.

00:25.000 --> 00:35.000
The topic of our meeting is management. We will discuss the main categories and approaches that exist in modern management,

00:35.000 --> 00:43.000
and also, in conclusion, we will focus on the trends of development that are present in the 21st century of management applicants.

00:44.000 --> 00:57.000
When we start talking about management, this topic has a long history, and in fact, all business success, all commercial success,

00:57.000 --> 01:07.000
are associated with successful organization of the process itself, with successful organization of the management process to achieve the goals that are before the company.

01:07.000 --> 01:16.000
Our task within this topic is, firstly, to get acquainted with the history of the emergence of management as a scientific discipline,

01:16.000 --> 01:30.000
secondly, to clarify the main concepts that are applied today, that have proven their effectiveness, that have proven their success, and that really give results.

01:31.000 --> 01:36.000
And the third task, as we have already said, will be to get acquainted with the prospects of management.

01:36.000 --> 01:45.000
Management does not stand still, it constantly develops, constantly changes, because it is forced to respond to the needs and requests of the external environment that are presented to it.

01:45.000 --> 01:58.000
And that is why only those who achieve success in business, who react very subtly and with caution to the problems that arise in the market,

01:58.000 --> 02:11.000
and who are able to foresee the methods of impact, the results, the management approaches that will prove their effectiveness, not now, but tomorrow, the day after tomorrow.

02:11.000 --> 02:18.000
This is the success of the achievements of those businessmen who have achieved outstanding results.

02:18.000 --> 02:30.000
When we talk about management, the first question that arises is related to the definition. What will we understand about management?

02:31.000 --> 02:39.000
This is a rather difficult question, because it can be approached from two points of view.

02:39.000 --> 02:44.000
The first point of view is to give some academic definition.

02:44.000 --> 02:58.000
We can open a large number of textbooks, and textbooks written by famous authors, who have undisputed and undisputed authority in this field,

02:58.000 --> 03:07.000
and see that each of these authors gives, albeit similar, but in some way different definition of management,

03:07.000 --> 03:13.000
and makes emphasis on different directions and approaches.

03:13.000 --> 03:22.000
Let's focus on the practically significant, practically applicable, practically verifiable definition of management.

03:22.000 --> 03:29.000
And then, when we will consider the formation of management, different theoretical approaches that are implemented in management,

03:29.000 --> 03:36.000
different achievements that are in management, then, accordingly, we will fill this definition with a specific meaning,

03:36.000 --> 03:41.000
in order not to indulge in any other academic nuances.

03:41.000 --> 03:48.000
Let's, within the framework of our meeting today, within the framework of considering the material of the topic,

03:48.000 --> 03:58.000
within the framework of considering the material of the course, we will consider management as a management of social-economic and social-technical systems,

03:58.000 --> 04:02.000
which has as its goal to obtain a specific result.

04:02.000 --> 04:07.000
What is important to pay attention to in this definition?

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
First of all, it is about systems.

04:09.000 --> 04:13.000
Modern management is a kind of system organization.

04:13.000 --> 04:20.000
There are no autonomous elements, no separate independent parts, independent blocks,

04:20.000 --> 04:25.000
which we can put together and get a certain management structure.

04:25.000 --> 04:26.000
Management is a system.

04:26.000 --> 04:31.000
This is the first and fundamental basis on which we should pay attention.

04:31.000 --> 04:33.000
Next.

04:33.000 --> 04:39.000
As for management, this management is primarily carried out by people,

04:39.000 --> 04:47.000
it encompasses people, and, accordingly, all management has a social structure, a social basis.

04:47.000 --> 04:51.000
Naturally, this social basis is primarily economic.

04:51.000 --> 04:58.000
We are talking about business, we are talking about commerce, we are talking about economic relations that arise in this process.

04:58.000 --> 05:05.000
But, in addition to these economic achievements, we are also talking about technical achievements.

05:05.000 --> 05:14.000
If we are talking about production, then, accordingly, we should consider the problem of technical devices,

05:14.000 --> 05:18.000
machines, machines on which telecommerce products are produced.

05:18.000 --> 05:24.000
If we are talking about services, then these services are also based on different technical achievements.

05:24.000 --> 05:32.000
Therefore, we will highlight in management both social-economic relations and social-technical relations.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
These are all the relations that exist in society.

05:34.000 --> 05:39.000
These are all the relations that have their own hierarchy, their own pattern.

05:39.000 --> 05:48.000
These are all the relations that are realized by people, between people, and which are realized in the process of our social interaction.

05:48.000 --> 05:53.000
But, again, we are talking about management from a practical point of view.

05:53.000 --> 05:59.000
We need to acquire the skills of applying these or other concepts of management,

05:59.000 --> 06:06.000
these or other management approaches, so that we can implement them in our everyday business activities.

06:06.000 --> 06:11.000
Our business activity is always oriented towards the result.

06:11.000 --> 06:20.000
We can build plans, we can build prospects, but these will be plans and prospects for achieving a specific final result.

06:20.000 --> 06:27.000
There is no business for the sake of a strategy, there is no business for the sake of some distant, clouded goals.

06:27.000 --> 06:33.000
These are some ideological moments, and this is what not businessmen do, but what politicians do.

06:33.000 --> 06:41.000
Every business is focused on the result, because the result is essentially the achievement that we have achieved.

06:41.000 --> 06:49.000
And then, when we bring this result to the market, then the position that is occupied by this market,

06:49.000 --> 06:56.000
the segmentation of the market that is taking place, the income that we receive,

06:56.000 --> 07:04.000
they testify whether we have achieved a profitable result, or even the most wonderful management,

07:04.000 --> 07:09.000
the most wonderful managerial relations and the wonderful psychological climate in the team,

07:09.000 --> 07:15.000
turned out to be ineffective, because the result that we have achieved is not in demand.

07:16.000 --> 07:22.000
Accordingly, the result is the important third feature that we will have in mind in management.

07:22.000 --> 07:25.000
So, the first thing is that management is always a system.

07:25.000 --> 07:34.000
The second thing is that management always has a social value, because it is associated with the relationships of people.

07:34.000 --> 07:42.000
Moreover, these are economic and technical relations, like the material basis on which management is implemented.

07:42.000 --> 07:53.000
And the third thing is the result. Only management, only those approaches in management that implement all these three features,

07:53.000 --> 08:00.000
turn out to be productive. In fact, these are the three basic, main points that we need to know,

08:00.000 --> 08:05.000
we need to remember when we make any management decision.

08:06.000 --> 08:15.000
If we do not pay attention to any of these three aspects, or we miss attention to this point,

08:15.000 --> 08:22.000
we level it, then, unfortunately, it will lead not to the results that we want.

08:22.000 --> 08:32.000
As you understand, I do not stop at this for a long time, because I would like us to come to the conclusion

08:32.000 --> 08:36.000
that management is a certain professional activity.

08:36.000 --> 08:46.000
Management is not the result of common sense, it is not what is given by God, what a person shows.

08:46.000 --> 08:56.000
Management is a daily, long-term work, and it is the professional activity that is expensive.

08:57.000 --> 09:03.000
Moreover, it is a professional activity, it concerns management of all processes built into organizations.

09:03.000 --> 09:14.000
And, what is also very important to pay attention to, business is always the situation that is realized in the conditions of risk and uncertainty.

09:14.000 --> 09:23.000
Unfortunately, or fortunately, we never know for sure what results we will get,

09:23.000 --> 09:31.000
and how much those plans that we have set for ourselves, how much those business plans that we have written down for ourselves will be realized.

09:31.000 --> 09:41.000
In the end, it is very difficult to take into account all that huge set of relations that is around the business.

09:41.000 --> 09:45.000
And very often we have to take risks, it is twofold.

09:45.000 --> 09:55.000
Either our risk is justified and we make a leap, and, in principle, what concerns the undisputed business achievements,

09:55.000 --> 09:57.000
it has always been a certain risk.

09:57.000 --> 10:02.000
This is the risk that Henry Ford had, this is the risk that Bill Gates had, this is the risk that Fayol had,

10:02.000 --> 10:05.000
what we will talk about today.

10:05.000 --> 10:11.000
And when they began to deal with their own questions, each with their own topic,

10:11.000 --> 10:19.000
and each of them did not know who we would study after 100 years, and who we would forget and not even remember.

10:19.000 --> 10:25.000
At the same time, in addition to the risk, there is a significant element of uncertainty.

10:25.000 --> 10:31.000
Again, if we put new goods on the market, if we try to build a new service,

10:31.000 --> 10:37.000
it is not always clear how much it will be in demand.

10:38.000 --> 10:45.000
We can make the most wonderful product, but it will not be in demand,

10:45.000 --> 10:51.000
because either the advertising will be poorly done, or the psychology of the consumer will not be taken into account.

10:51.000 --> 10:59.000
This is a very important point that we will also talk about and which the manager and management specialist should also consider.

10:59.000 --> 11:04.000
So, all this situation is associated with uncertainty.

11:04.000 --> 11:11.000
This is a situation where either we are on a horse, or we need to start all over again,

11:11.000 --> 11:15.000
and the funds that we have invested may not be repaid.

11:15.000 --> 11:21.000
I think I do not need to talk about this in more detail for you, people who do business every day.

11:21.000 --> 11:29.000
At the same time, in order to function normally in a situation of risk and uncertainty,

11:29.000 --> 11:33.000
the manager must have some freedom.

11:33.000 --> 11:41.000
Here, an administrative approach is not allowed, when you have a plan and you have to do exactly as it is written.

11:41.000 --> 11:48.000
It is not allowed because the documents are written once and for all.

11:48.000 --> 11:57.000
They reflect some of the conditions that were before, but these documents do not reflect the changes that are now.

11:58.000 --> 12:03.000
Accordingly, if we work on the basis of the past, we remain in the past.

12:03.000 --> 12:08.000
Only those who achieve success in business, only those who are successful managers,

12:08.000 --> 12:15.000
who react very subtly and subtly to the everyday changes that are happening,

12:15.000 --> 12:22.000
and for this you need a certain freedom in making both strategic and tactical decisions.

12:23.000 --> 12:30.000
Because it determines the direction in which economic investment will be made,

12:30.000 --> 12:35.000
the direction in which a particular production system will be built,

12:35.000 --> 12:42.000
a particular operating system, where certain or other prospects will be determined.

12:42.000 --> 12:47.000
And the manager must take all this into account, he must understand all this,

12:48.000 --> 12:53.000
and accordingly he is given a certain degree of freedom,

12:53.000 --> 13:00.000
but for this degree of freedom he must pay for the achievement of the end results.

13:00.000 --> 13:08.000
It is all these circumstances that show that a manager must represent himself and represents himself

13:08.000 --> 13:12.000
in the whole civilized world a professional sphere of activity,

13:12.000 --> 13:15.000
which must be studied for a long time, first of all, at the university,

13:15.000 --> 13:20.000
getting basic knowledge of theory, but the main thing is that all achievements,

13:20.000 --> 13:24.000
all success of a manager is associated with our specific experience.

13:24.000 --> 13:29.000
We can all read the same books, but we will all apply them in different ways,

13:29.000 --> 13:31.000
and we will all get different results.

13:31.000 --> 13:36.000
This is the most expensive thing that is called experience,

13:36.000 --> 13:40.000
which is the essential basis of professionalism.

13:41.000 --> 13:46.000
We have now determined the understanding of management,

13:46.000 --> 13:49.000
which will be present in our presentation today.

13:49.000 --> 13:55.000
Let's now focus on the main functions of management.

13:55.000 --> 13:58.000
We have considered its main characteristics, its tasks,

13:58.000 --> 14:03.000
the conditions in which it is implemented, the conditions of risk, management,

14:03.000 --> 14:07.000
the conditions of freedom of choice, tactical and strategic decisions

14:07.000 --> 14:09.000
for achieving the desired result.

14:09.000 --> 14:13.000
Let's now move on to the functional consideration of management,

14:13.000 --> 14:17.000
because management is, first of all, a system of relations,

14:17.000 --> 14:20.000
and this system has some functions.

14:20.000 --> 14:23.000
There is no management at all.

14:23.000 --> 14:26.000
Management should always be specific.

14:26.000 --> 14:31.000
As for the function of management, different authors highlight different functions.

14:31.000 --> 14:34.000
Again, this is natural, we have discussed this with you.

14:34.000 --> 14:41.000
But from a pragmatic point of view, from the point of view of our daily business tasks,

14:41.000 --> 14:46.000
which we must solve from the point of view of organizing any business processes,

14:46.000 --> 14:50.000
we can highlight four main functions of management.

14:50.000 --> 14:54.000
In fact, these are the functions that are highlighted by different authors.

14:54.000 --> 14:57.000
They can be called differently, they can be given in different order.

14:57.000 --> 15:03.000
This is not so important, because we need to consider the functional tasks

15:03.000 --> 15:08.000
and each of them, depending on the tasks that are in front of it,

15:08.000 --> 15:13.000
depending on the conditions on the market that exist,

15:13.000 --> 15:18.000
will highlight those or other functions from the point of view of their priorities,

15:18.000 --> 15:20.000
from the point of view of their importance.

15:20.000 --> 15:25.000
The question is that management should include all these four functions.

15:25.000 --> 15:30.000
Just at every specific moment, in every specific situation,

15:30.000 --> 15:35.000
each of these functions can have a more important meaning.

15:35.000 --> 15:39.000
Another meaning can wait, not cancel, not disappear,

15:39.000 --> 15:44.000
but simply reorient itself from the point of view of their priorities.

15:44.000 --> 15:49.000
As for the function of management, as we have already discussed,

15:49.000 --> 15:52.000
planning is of great importance.

15:52.000 --> 15:59.000
Management is a system of management relationships that arise between people

15:59.000 --> 16:02.000
that are oriented to the production that exists.

16:02.000 --> 16:08.000
Therefore, management is associated with planning of activities.

16:08.000 --> 16:12.000
I have to organize the planning of people's busyness.

16:12.000 --> 16:15.000
I have to organize the planning of the busyness of production.

16:15.000 --> 16:20.000
I have to organize the planning of providing the implementation of a particular service.

16:20.000 --> 16:23.000
Accordingly, when we talk about planning,

16:23.000 --> 16:30.000
it is the tactical, close and strategic long-term goals that we set for ourselves.

16:30.000 --> 16:37.000
Because depending on the goals, the plans, the tasks I set for myself,

16:37.000 --> 16:43.000
I will have a further management system.

16:43.000 --> 16:51.000
Therefore, planning is a certain perspective that I need to achieve

16:51.000 --> 16:54.000
and the steps of achieving this perspective.

16:54.000 --> 16:58.000
These are not just plans that I will set.

16:58.000 --> 17:02.000
This is not a certain result that I have previously developed,

17:02.000 --> 17:06.000
for example, a state plan for a five-year, ten-year or something else.

17:06.000 --> 17:15.000
Planning is the desired result and the ways, methods, steps, operations to achieve it.

17:15.000 --> 17:19.000
It is very important that the result does not detract from practice.

17:19.000 --> 17:23.000
You can set the most remarkable result,

17:23.000 --> 17:27.000
doubling of the internal product, triple, and so on,

17:27.000 --> 17:32.000
but until specific ways of this achievement are prescribed,

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
and the ways that are implemented,

17:34.000 --> 17:37.000
again, not some ideal schemes that can be read in any textbook,

17:37.000 --> 17:46.000
but really those methods that are able to be achieved.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.000
So, planning.

17:49.000 --> 17:52.000
After we have planned the activity,

17:52.000 --> 17:57.000
planned certain perspectives, certain approaches, certain tasks,

17:57.000 --> 18:00.000
the stage of organization comes,

18:00.000 --> 18:04.000
the organization of achieving these plans.

18:04.000 --> 18:07.000
The plan only then matters,

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
I have already emphasized and I will emphasize it again,

18:10.000 --> 18:12.000
because for business it is a fundamental approach.

18:12.000 --> 18:17.000
The plan only then matters when there are ways of its achievement.

18:17.000 --> 18:20.000
But after these ways are prescribed,

18:20.000 --> 18:26.000
it is necessary to organize their material achievements, their implementation.

18:26.000 --> 18:29.000
The plan can be the most remarkable,

18:29.000 --> 18:33.000
the ways of its achievement can also be remarkably prescribed,

18:33.000 --> 18:36.000
but its execution, the execution of the plan,

18:36.000 --> 18:39.000
the achievement of the results is carried out by people.

18:39.000 --> 18:45.000
The achievement of the results should always be tied to people,

18:45.000 --> 18:48.000
both to the manufacturers and to the suppliers,

18:48.000 --> 18:51.000
and in the end to those who will use these results,

18:51.000 --> 18:55.000
that is, for whom this whole business scheme is completed.

18:57.000 --> 19:02.000
As for the organization, the execution of the results,

19:02.000 --> 19:04.000
organizational management,

19:04.000 --> 19:10.000
perhaps this is one of the most difficult tasks of management,

19:10.000 --> 19:17.000
because this is the practice of achieving results.

19:17.000 --> 19:20.000
This is direct work with people,

19:20.000 --> 19:23.000
this is a direct organization of production,

19:23.000 --> 19:26.000
this is a direct conclusion,

19:26.000 --> 19:31.000
the exit to the market of those or other results that were obtained.

19:31.000 --> 19:35.000
We will talk about this more than once.

19:35.000 --> 19:41.000
The next function of management is, of course, the function of motivation.

19:41.000 --> 19:49.000
We work with people, this is the original idea that should be constantly kept in mind.

19:49.000 --> 19:52.000
We do not work with money, not with machines,

19:52.000 --> 19:57.000
we work with people, with their desires, needs, abilities,

19:57.000 --> 20:05.000
with their desire to get something, with their laziness, with their ambitions.

20:05.000 --> 20:08.000
We work with real people,

20:08.000 --> 20:14.000
and these people need to be motivated to solve the tasks that we have set for them,

20:14.000 --> 20:18.000
that we have planned for them, that we have organized for their execution.

20:18.000 --> 20:26.000
And it is necessary to achieve that people are motivated to achieve the results

20:26.000 --> 20:28.000
that are ahead of them.

20:28.000 --> 20:34.000
They sabotaged them, they tried to get rid of them, they worked with a cold.

20:34.000 --> 20:42.000
I think that the problem of motivation is something that everyone is well aware of.

20:42.000 --> 20:44.000
How to motivate a person?

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
Is one salary enough?

20:46.000 --> 20:49.000
Or do you need some additional results?

20:49.000 --> 20:54.000
Bonuses, payment of loans, medical care.

20:54.000 --> 20:57.000
Is material stimulation enough?

20:57.000 --> 20:59.000
Or do we need non-material stimulation?

20:59.000 --> 21:05.000
All of this is also a significant function of management,

21:05.000 --> 21:09.000
because a successful management result,

21:09.000 --> 21:16.000
a successful system of building relationships in an organization,

21:16.000 --> 21:18.000
is determined by motivation.

21:18.000 --> 21:24.000
A well-organized motivation allows you to get long-term results.

21:24.000 --> 21:28.000
A well-organized motivation allows you to avoid current frameworks.

21:28.000 --> 21:35.000
A well-organized motivation allows you to achieve a re-execution of plans

21:35.000 --> 21:38.000
and, accordingly, to get more and more results,

21:38.000 --> 21:42.000
which will strengthen the position of the company in the market,

21:42.000 --> 21:49.000
to help promote its brand and to get the desired results for the company.

21:51.000 --> 21:56.000
And, of course, when we talk about management functions,

21:56.000 --> 22:01.000
we should pay attention to its function as a control.

22:01.000 --> 22:08.000
Indeed, we can build wonderful plans with all the conditions we talked about.

22:08.000 --> 22:14.000
We can organize the whole system of execution of these plans.

22:14.000 --> 22:17.000
We can build a great motivation system.

22:17.000 --> 22:24.000
But we need to control all these actions, all these results.

22:24.000 --> 22:29.000
Do they lead us to the final result we want to achieve?

22:29.000 --> 22:35.000
Because we can get a lot of intermediate results.

22:35.000 --> 22:40.000
A good motivation can lead to the growth of loyalty of the company employees,

22:40.000 --> 22:43.000
to the division of their missions in the company.

22:43.000 --> 22:48.000
They will not formally carry out their duties,

22:48.000 --> 22:53.000
but the results that will be obtained in the end

22:53.000 --> 22:57.000
will differ from the initial tasks that were before us.

22:57.000 --> 23:03.000
Somewhere there was a failure or a deviation.

23:03.000 --> 23:09.000
And we need a constant feedback at every stage.

23:09.000 --> 23:13.000
At the stage of planning, at the stage of organization, at the stage of motivation.

23:13.000 --> 23:17.000
We must constantly control the current results

23:17.000 --> 23:21.000
with the final results that we have determined for ourselves,

23:21.000 --> 23:24.000
which we have set as the organizers of the production,

23:24.000 --> 23:27.000
as managers, as the owners of a particular business.

23:28.000 --> 23:32.000
And as for the control, this is also a very delicate point.

23:32.000 --> 23:36.000
There are different forms of control, which we will talk about in a moment.

23:36.000 --> 23:41.000
And this control should not be something like a supervisor.

23:41.000 --> 23:49.000
As for the control, we are not only talking about tracking the implementation of the tasks,

23:49.000 --> 23:55.000
but also about identifying mistakes, identifying difficulties that arise along the way,

23:55.000 --> 24:00.000
analyzing these difficulties and, accordingly, correcting them.

24:00.000 --> 24:06.000
In this case, the control receives a wide field of distribution,

24:06.000 --> 24:12.000
which is not only related to tracking the accuracy of the result,

24:12.000 --> 24:18.000
but also to modification, adaptation of this result,

24:18.000 --> 24:20.000
adding of certain resources.

24:20.000 --> 24:24.000
Because we work in a situation of risk, in a situation of uncertainty.

24:24.000 --> 24:29.000
And, accordingly, we do not always know what difficulties we have encountered.

24:29.000 --> 24:33.000
If we encounter difficulties, then control is needed

24:33.000 --> 24:40.000
so that we can solve this difficulty, level it, disavow it as early as possible,

24:40.000 --> 24:44.000
until it leads to a stop of production,

24:44.000 --> 24:48.000
when it leads to the failure of the brand on the market, and so on.

24:48.000 --> 24:52.000
Control should not be all-encompassing and constant.

24:52.000 --> 24:57.000
Control should be optimal, it should be productive,

24:57.000 --> 25:03.000
it should be progressive from the point of view that it is aimed at achieving

25:03.000 --> 25:07.000
the ultimate goal that is before any management.

25:07.000 --> 25:11.000
Achieving the result that was set, for which the business is organized,

25:11.000 --> 25:15.000
for which efforts are made, funds are invested,

25:15.000 --> 25:18.000
for which people working in this industry are working.

25:19.000 --> 25:23.000
So, these are the main management functions,

25:23.000 --> 25:26.000
which are traditionally highlighted in it.

25:26.000 --> 25:37.000
And usually, few practitioners will argue with these functions.

25:37.000 --> 25:41.000
As for the theorists, they also agree with these functions.

25:41.000 --> 25:47.000
Just as I have already noted, different nuances, different aspects are highlighted in different functions.

25:47.000 --> 25:54.000
This, however, depends on the specific production, on the specific tasks that we face.

25:54.000 --> 26:02.000
So, this is what concerns the basic management positions,

26:02.000 --> 26:08.000
how we will consider them, and the functions that we will face in management.

